-- Open SQL Server Configuration Manager\n-- Navigate to SQL Server Network Configuration -> Protocols for <InstanceName>\n-- Right-click 'Protocols for <InstanceName>' and select 'Properties'\n-- Go to the 'Flags' tab, and set 'Force Encryption' to 'Yes'\n\n-- Ensure you have a valid SSL certificate installed on the server\n-- Restart the SQL Server service to apply changes\n\n-- In your connection string, specify encryption:\nServer=myServerAddress;Database=myDataBase;User Id=myUsername;Password=myPassword;Encrypt=True;